,<br />then you should add the appropriate built-time assert to *your* code.<br />Not to some random generic function that others care about and that<br />others do _not_ have problems with.<br /><br />So if you have a data structure in virtio that is<br />architecture-dependent and might not be a word size, you add the<br /><br />   BUILD_BUG_ON(sizeof(mytype) &gt; sizeof(long));<br /><br />or whatever. With a big comment saying "this needs to actually fit in<br />a single register so that we can do atomic accesses".<br /><br />You do not screw it up for everybody else.<br /><br />                Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
